snippet.textDisplay: Segment really shows how skillful Orton's heel work is. The way he teased jumping on his neck (aided by the camerawork) before using the chair on Edge's back, it's the simple things that make the difference. When it comes to the art of how to carry yourself when the other wrestlers on the deck, whether it be in segments or within matches, no-one does it quite like Orton. He's like a predator tenderizing prey - after all these years it's still unsettling.... and very, VERY effective.
